entry.def: If things clack or if you clack them, they make a short loud noise, especially when they hit each other.

example.ex: The windshield wipers clacked back and forth...
example.tran: 挡风玻璃上的雨刷咔嗒咔嗒来回摆动。

example.ex: I clacked one ski against the other and almost tripped.
example.tran: 我的一个雪橇板咔嗒一声撞在另一个上面，差点把我绊倒。

means.word_mean: 1. a sharp abrupt noise as if two objects hit together; may be repeated
2. a simple valve with a hinge on one side; allows fluid to flow in only one direction
2. make a clucking sounds, characteristic of hens
3. speak (about unimportant matters) rapidly and incessantly
